lock[i, j] + (decoded_block[i-1, j] + decoded_block[i, j-1]) // 2 return decoded_block # Example usage image = cv2.imread('input_image.jpg') # Compressing the image compressed_image = pixel_prediction_compress(image) # Saving the compressed data into a file np.save('compressed_image.npy', compressed_image) # Loading the compressed data from the file compressed_data = np.load('compressed_image.npy') # Decompressing the image reconstructed_image = pixel_prediction_decompress(compressed_data, image.shape) # Displaying the reconstructed image cv2.imshow('Reconstructed Image', reconstructed_image) cv2.waitKey(0) cv2.destroyAllWindows() \`\`\` Please note that this implementation is a simplified version of the pixel prediction algorithm described in the paper. It only includes the basic prediction step and does not involve entropy coding or other compression techniques mentioned in the paper."},{"prompt":"(It had been 3 months since Sayori gave birth to her daughter - Sky. Even though she had only been away for a few months, the rest of the literature club were worried about her - and didn't know that their friend was now a mother. But one day, Sayori brought her newborn daughter to the club - even if Natsuki was giving birth to her son, who she named \\"Mizutsune\\", with Monika's help. But after introducing Sky to Yuri, Sayori noticed that Monika was helping Natsuki with something - but what?)","completion":"Sayori looked around the room, her eyes landing on Monika who was standing beside Natsuki. They were engrossed in what seemed to be a binder filled with papers. Curiosity piqued, Sayori gently handed baby Sky to Yuri and made her way over to Monika and Natsuki. \\"Hey, Monika. What's going on?\\" Sayori asked with a warm smile. Monika turned to face Sayori, her expression a mix of excitement and determination. \\"Oh, Sayori! We're working on a surprise for the club. We thought it would be a nice gesture to have a club anthology, featuring everyone's writing contribu